  "texts": [
    "We assessed each model's performance using the F 1 -score, a commonly used metric that averages precision and recall:",
    "In the context of this work, TP represents the number of correctly identified phases (true positives), FP is the number of phases incorrectly identified (false positives), and FN is the number missed phases (false negatives).",
    "A high F 1 -score, close to 1, indicates that the model can effectively identify all phases in a sample without incorrectly identifying phases that are not present.",
    "The results from each model trained on XRD patterns or virtual PDFs are shown in Fig. 2, where the bar heights (y-axis) represent F 1 -scores and",
    "Fig. 1 | Combined analysis of XRD patterns and PDFs."
